Hi. We previously had the "Abandoned transaction found - run hg recover" issue a few days ago which was fixed.  (As mentioned in BCLOUD-10024, same repository)

The repository: https://bitbucket.org/plutora/portal

Now however, we are receiving a "HTTP Error: 400 (Bad request)" whenever we are trying to pull code through tortoise hg (Me and multiple developers). This may have been caused by me closing a lot of branches because it was working fine during my process of closing them, and then tried to pull again but started to receive this error. When trying to build teamcity, it does not work because of this error either.

I initially did a

{code}
#!python

&#x27;hg rollback&#x27;
{code}

on my localhost and it seemed to fix my problem, but the "HTTP Error: 400 (Bad request)" came back and we are still unable to build through teamcity.

Looking through some previous tickets, here are some information.\\
Using

{code}
#!python

hg pull --debug -v
{code}

, I receive:

{code}
#!python

using https://bitbucket.org/plutora/portal
http auth: user MartinPurnomo, password not set
sending capabilities command
bitbucket.org certificate successfully verified
bitbucket.org certificate successfully verified
pulling from https://MartinPurnomo@bitbucket.org/plutora/portal
preparing listkeys for "bookmarks"
sending listkeys command
query 1; heads
sending batch command
searching for changes
all local heads known remotely
sending getbundle command
HTTP Error: 400 (Bad request)
{code}

When running

{code}
#!python

hg verify
{code}

,

{code}
#!python

checking changesets
checking manifests
crosschecking files in changesets and manifests
checking files
27175 files, 15204 changesets, 79250 total revisions
{code}

Using Mercurial version: 3.0.2\\
Topological Heads: 769 (Another dev has 773)

Note: I&#x27;m still able to commit and push code.

Thanks in Advanced.

If you look at [this commit|https://bitbucket.org/dresearchfe/hipos-dfe/commits/891321cca14df7a788b2660f4140493320398e50] with a git diff, you&#x27;ll see that the change created a complete rewrite of the file because each line has now {{
}} instead of the previous {{
}}. This is annoying because this file is no longer readable the same way with the same tools and the commit diff can&#x27;t tell you what actually was the change. Please let the online editor use the normal {{
}}, at least when the file already uses {{
}} instead of {{
}}. I personally also believe that there is no reason to spend two bytes to say what one byte can say, but I accept if other people think differently about their text files.

Also easily noticeable with a git diff are a few space chars that are not necessary. The bitbucket diff doesn&#x27;t show them. A simple regex can match and kill all trailing space chars automatically without changing the meaning of most text files.

(I leave the priority on major. Don&#x27;t know about you guys but for me personally such kind of result critical ;))

Nowdocs like

{code}
#!PHP

<?php
echo <<<&#x27;EOT&#x27;
My name is "$name". I am printing some $foo->foo.
Now, I am printing some {$foo->bar[1]}.
This should not print a capital &#x27;A&#x27;: \x41
EOT;
?>
{code}

are not highlighted correctly.

See [here|http://php.net/manual/en/language.types.string.php#language.types.string.syntax.nowdoc] for the according PHP documentation.

My branch is called "feature/test" and no matter how I try to hit the:
{noformat}
GET https://bitbucket.org/api/2.0/repositories/{owner}/{repo_slug}/commit/{revision}
{noformat}
API with this, it will not bend. Replacing the "/" with %2F does not work.

Google helped me find https://bitbucket.org/site/master/issue/408/branches-and-tags-with-slashes-in-their where this seems to have been fixed for every other API call except this one.

I&#x27;d like to know if there is a plan for this to be fixed, or if there is another way I can get the commit SHA for the tip of a branch whose name has a slash.
